      summary: 'Postpartum care is the care you receive after having your baby, helping your body recover while you learn to care for your newborn.',
      explanation: `**What to Expect After Delivery:**

*Physical Changes:*
- Vaginal bleeding (lochia) for 4-6 weeks
- Cramping as uterus shrinks (afterpains)
- Breast engorgement when milk comes in
- Soreness from delivery (vaginal or cesarean)
- Tiredness and need for rest

*Emotional Changes:*
- "Baby blues" (mood swings, crying) in first 2 weeks - very common
- Bonding with your baby
- Adjustment to new role

**Recovery Tips:**
- Rest when baby sleeps
- Accept help from family and friends
- Eat nutritious foods
- Stay hydrated
- Don't lift heavy things
- Take care of incision (if cesarean) or tears

**When to Call Your Doctor:**
- Heavy bleeding (soaking a pad in 1 hour)
- Fever over 100.4F
- Severe headache
- Chest pain or trouble breathing
- Redness, swelling, or discharge from incision
- Thoughts of harming yourself or baby
- Feeling very sad, anxious, or hopeless for more than 2 weeks

**Postpartum Visit:**
- Usually 4-6 weeks after delivery
- Check your recovery
- Discuss contraception
- Screen for depression`,
