      explanation: `**Fourth Trimester Model:**

*Redefining Postpartum Care:*
- Initial contact within 3 weeks (not waiting until 6 weeks)
- Multiple touchpoints throughout 12 weeks
- Comprehensive visit by 12 weeks
- Transition to well-woman care

*Components:*
- Physical recovery assessment
- Mood and emotional wellbeing
- Infant care and breastfeeding
- Contraception and future pregnancy planning
- Chronic disease management
- Healthcare transition

**Addressing Maternal Mortality:**

*Leading Causes (US):*
- Hemorrhage
- Cardiovascular conditions
- Cardiomyopathy
- Infection/sepsis
- Venous thromboembolism
- Hypertensive disorders
- Mental health conditions (including suicide)

*60% occur postpartum, many preventable*

*Quality Initiatives:*
- Maternal mortality review committees
- Severe maternal morbidity tracking
- Standardized safety bundles (AIM)
- Enhanced postpartum monitoring for high-risk

**Disparities in Postpartum Outcomes:**

*Documented Inequities:*
- Black women 3-4x higher mortality
- Delayed recognition of complications
- Differences in postpartum visit attendance
- Barriers to breastfeeding support

*Mitigation:*
- Implicit bias training
- Community doula programs
- Home visiting programs
- Standardized protocols
- Patient navigation

**Integrated Mental Health:**

*Collaborative Care Models:*
- Screening in OB setting
- Warm handoffs to mental health
- Co-located services
- Telepsychiatry options

*Treatment in Pregnancy/Postpartum:*
- Psychotherapy (IPT, CBT) effective
- SSRIs (sertraline, citalopram) preferred if medication needed
- Risk-benefit discussion
- Close monitoring

**Extended Postpartum Contraception Access:**

*Immediate Postplacental IUD:*
- Safe and effective
- Higher expulsion rate (offset by increased access)
- Particularly important for high-risk patients

*12-Month Postpartum Prescription:*
- Ensure contraception access through postpartum year
- Insurance coverage considerations

**Innovative Care Models:**
- Group postpartum care
- Telehealth visits
- Home visiting programs
- Postpartum support groups
- Peer counseling
- Doula support throughout postpartum`,
